latestIgtvVideos.caption:

The age-old idea that casual and diamonds don't mix has officially been demystified, courtesy of celebrity stylist Tanya Ghavri (@tanghavri) who tells us how there is something beautifully tasteful about pairing denim with diamonds.

latestIgtvVideos.title: How To Style: Everyday Diamonds | Vogue India x Natural Diamond Council
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
No longer shelved away for just extravagant soirées, diamonds today reflect the ethos of an evolving fashion landscape – one that identifies natural diamonds as part of everyday wear. Be it dressing high-low, like wearing stackable bracelets with your pantsuit or going for an everyday casual look with a pair of diamond studs and a graphic tee, diamonds lend a timeless charm to just about anything, and stylist Deepshikha Khanna (@dailystylematters) shows us one too many ways on how to make diamonds a part of our everyday fashion discourse. 

@onlynaturaldiamonds_in #VogueNDCDiamondFest #VogueXOnlyNaturalDiamonds

When Anupama Parameswaran was younger, she longed for the grace of Raja Ravi Varma’s muses, wishing, quietly, to carry it as her own. For our January-February cover, this dream is actualised as the actor is reimagined as Padmini, the lotus nymph, immortalised on Varma’s canvas. In conversation with the star, we explore the quiet details of a loud life. 

Read the full story at the link in bio.

#Exclusive: Actors @_prat and @priyabanerjee tied the knot in an intimate wedding ceremony at the groom’s mother, the late actor Smita Patil’s home in Bandra, Mumbai. “We desired a ‘ghar ki shaadi’, and getting married to the love of my life here—the first house that my mom bought and my home—was the best way to honour her in spirit,” reveals Prateik Smita Patil. 

The couple wore custom @taruntahiliani ensembles for the ceremony. The bride walked down the aisle in an ivory and gold lehenga with a corset and jewellery by Khurana Jewellery House. The groom complemented her in an open sherwani, a signature drape shirt, and a dhoti set. Swipe to see a first look.
 
Photographed by @thehouseontheclouds

latestPosts.caption:
Shalini Peiris (@i.am.shalini.p) will never forget the moment she found out about her casting. The actor, born in the hill town of Kandy in Sri Lanka and currently based out of London, had just landed in the British capital after shooting in Serbia and turned on her phone to see a missed call from her manager. Peiris loved the show so much, she had seen both seasons twice over and was happy just to be able to audition for the new season. But as destiny would have it, she got the part—a culmination of a journey that began nearly 15 years ago.

At the link in bio, the actor talks about how she wishes to nurture the industry back home and champion Sri Lankan stories.

Photographed by Jacquetta Clark (@jacquettaclark)
Words by Mansher Dhillon (@thanks4shering)

latestPosts.caption:
Valentine’s Day lost its charm right around the time classroom card exchanges stopped being a thing. No more glitter heart stickers, no more best friend-approved candy and handpicked flower trades—just an avalanche of over-the-top romance that feels more like a performance than a celebration. If the holiday hasn’t felt the same since childhood, you’re not alone—head to the link in bio for a real take on why February 14 may have peaked when we were ten.

Representative image

latestPosts.caption:
With the gazillion meetings you’re pulled into every week, adding one more to the list might seem excessive. But your therapist would probably disagree. If you’re in a long-term committed relationship, you may not realize that the constant discussion about your financial goals, holiday plans, or family planning can easily drain the romance from your quality time. A scheduled meeting can be life-changing for anyone who’s partnered up. “Now we save the stressful stuff for our check-ins so we can actually enjoy our couch time and date nights,” says Julia Ries, who introduced this practice into her marriage.
Swipe to know more about how to plan and participate in your couple’s meeting.

Photographed by Tarun Vishwa (@tarunvishwaofficial)

latestPosts.caption:
Being happy for a friend is easy when life is going well, but what happens when their wins highlight everything you’re struggling with? The dream job, the engagement, the three-bedroom house—while you truly want to celebrate them, it can feel like a reminder of what you don’t have. It’s a feeling no one talks about, but it doesn’t make you a bad friend. At the link in bio, experts share how to navigate these emotions, show up for your friends, and celebrate their success without losing sight of your own.

Photographed by Bhumika Sharma (@akimuhb_)

#VogueCulture

@thombrowne revealed his collection at the 
#NewYorkFashionWeek with a theatrical show featuring hundreds of paper cranes and a couple of oversized coats. The designer loosened up his famous proportions to offer roomy jackets and coats in brown, made from traditional suiting fabrics.

• @michaelkors’s collection took inspiration from “dégagé” feeling—a sense of ease. It’s a French word, but, said Kors, it’s an undeniably New York thing. Such rang true of his generously cut tailoring, roomy knit separates, and even sequin tunics proposed for the evening.

• Raul Lopez named his @luar fall 2025 collection Pato. In Spanish, pato means duck, as in the bird, but in some parts of Latin America, such as Puerto Rico, it’s a homophobic slur. “I wanted to reclaim that word,” said Lopez in his studio the day before his show took place.

Swipe to see the looks.
